article.headline: Pacific 86, UC Riverside 66
article.story: STOCKTON, Calif. (AP) -- -Reggie Vezia scored 15 points and had a career-high nine rebounds to lead Pacific to an 86-66 victory over UC Riverside Saturday night. Steffan Johnson and Ben Pemberton each scored 13 points for the Tigers(9-14, 5-5 Big West), who pulled away with a 19-3 run early in the second half. Anthony Esparza had 11 points and a game-high six assists for Pacific, which led 65-43 midway through the second half and never saw its lead fall below14 points the remainder of the game. Freshman Henrik Thomsen scored a game-high 28 points to lead UC Riverside(5-19, 1-9). Larry Cunningham had 19 points for the Highlanders. Pacific made 63 percent of its shots from the field in the second half and dominated inside with a 44-24 advantage in points in the paint. The Tigers also had a 43-25 rebounding edge. Pacific went on a 10-0 run to take its first lead six minutes into the game, then followed that with a 13-2 spurt to take its biggest lead of the first half at 32-18 with five minutes to play before the break. Riverside cut the margin to 10 points at halftime, then crept within 40-35 three minutes into the second half before the Tigers assumed command and turned the game into a blowout.
